ield_12310250":null,"progress":{"progress":0,"total":0},"comment":{"startAt":0,"maxResults":8,"total":8,"comments":[{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/issue/12694933/comment/13900118","id":"13900118","author":{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=shaie","name":"shaie","emailAddress":"serera at gmail dot com","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452","24x24":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452","16x16":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10452","32x32":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10452"},"displayName":"Shai Erera","active":true},"body":"I see that in Lucene45DVP, all access to addressInstances is guarded, so I think we should guard ramBytesUsed too. Likewise for ordIndexInstances. But when I look at Lucene4DVP, ramBytesUsed is an AtomicLong, and updated whenever a new DV is added ... can't we do the same? Also, looks like the computation of ramBytesUsed is slightly wrong, as it uses Integer.SIZE which is the number of bits in an int, not bytes.","updateAuthor":{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=shaie","name":"shaie","emailAddress":"serera at gmail dot com","avatarUrls":{"48x48":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=10452","24x24":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=10452","16x16":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=10452","32x32":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=10452"},"displayName":"Shai Erera","active":true},"created":"2014-02-13T08:15:14.591+0000","updated":"2014-02-13T08:15:14.591+0000"},{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/issue/12694933/comment/13900120","id":"13900120","author":{"self":"https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=thetaphi","name":"thetaphi","emailAddress":"uw